  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nI've read due to faulty random generators collisions in choice of k value during signing with ECDSA might occur (resulting in potential for secret key recovery from signed transactions, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elliptic_Curve_Digital_Signature_Algorithm#Security), same source claims that using https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6979.html when signing transaction prevents this issue.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nImplementation might be in `geth` code replacing random k selection with one based on RFC-6979 or adding global option to choose random vs deterministic RFC-6979 based.\r\n\r\nI want to help implementing this feature if provided help to locating signer code.",
